      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "APPEAL (2) got the job done again after enjoying a good run to make it two on end, scoring by one length (30.25) at this track over 520m. Has never missed the frame from six starts from this draw, including four wins. Form reads well for this. ZIPPING MEHARY (1) has shown good improvement at his last two starts, breaking through last time at Capalaba over 366m. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from three starts. One of the leading chances again. GONZO (6) was sent out big odds but was a fast winner (29.79) last time in a Grade 6 at this track. The form from his last run stacks up well. Should be in this for a long way. CANYA AURORA (8) has claims if she runs up to her best.",
